                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>This inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">52nd year</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Vijaya-Nandivarman.</hi> It records the death of <hi rend="bold">Gaṅgadiyaraiyar Kaṉṉāḍu Peruṅgaṅgar,</hi> (the chief) of <hi rend="bold">Kaṟkāṭṭūr,</hi> who at the instance of his uncle <hi rend="italic">(māmaḍi),</hi> the Bāṇa chief, fought on the occasion of the Pallava invasion against <hi rend="bold">Perumānaḍigaḷ</hi> (i.e. the Western Gaṅga king), when (the fortress of) <hi rend="bold">Peṇkuḻikkōṭṭai</hi> was destroyed. From the high regnal year quoted in the inscription, the king may be identified with Nandivarman Pallavamalla.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
